  "Choosing individual stocks within a single sector": "",
  "Transferring assets between brokerage accounts": "",
  "The distribution of investments across different asset classes such as stocks, bonds, and cash": "",
  "Asset allocation is the strategic mix of stocks, bonds, cash, and other investments in your portfolio. Research shows it accounts for roughly 90% of portfolio performance variation over time.": "",
  "$100,000 invested in an index fund with a 0.1% expense ratio vs. an actively managed fund with a 1% expense ratio, both returning 7% gross over 30 years. The index fund grows to approximately $740,000 while the active fund reaches $574,000. How much is lost to the higher fees?": "",
